The leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D04FFD64757C187F894AEE6B24A" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[399,443,1861,1882]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EA95FFD64757C187F894AEE6B24A" box="[399,443,1861,1882]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">Aloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× 
<emphasis id="B921EA95FFD64757C1C7F894AD43B24A" box="[463,542,1861,1882]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">selmarii</emphasis>
are purple-infused, but also, like those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D04FFD64757C3B3F897AB75B24A" box="[955,1064,1861,1883]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davyana">
<emphasis id="B921EA95FFD64757C3B3F897AB75B24A" box="[955,1064,1861,1883]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">A. davyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, borne erectly, not near-horizontal as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D04FFD64757C080F8BBAE6FB26E" authorityName="Schonland" authorityYear="1907" box="[136,306,1897,1919]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvibracteata">
<emphasis id="B921EA95FFD64757C080F8BBAE6FB26E" box="[136,306,1897,1919]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">A. parvibracteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Photograph: Gideon F. Smith.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2A660FFFD74756C080F870AEF5B2CB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5546861" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5546861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5546861/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" startId="7.[136,229,1953,1975]" targetBox="[173,1414,190,1929]" targetPageId="7">
